# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
By looking at the test cases we need a solution in nlogn.So we can try binary search. And when we think about binary search in this question We can easily thought of our solution.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We will use Binary in the ranges of min and max element of nums. And we try to find the total cost at the middle element and middle + 1 And then we compare there total cost whichever is smallest we will go to the side.
