Today is Wednesday. Hard Wednesday!!!
Let me translate into the form what I can understand.
Consider the function
$$
f(x)=\sum_i |nums[i]-x|cost[i]
$$
Find min(f(x)) where x is an integer, of course x must be between min(nums) and max(nums). At least, a brute force method is possible!

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here we provide several approaches. One is binary approach, other is using weighted median! The approach using derivative is also possible.
