# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We first sort the nums array and this makes sure that if we are at a particular index say i, then to convert all numbers in the array with index < i to nums[i], then we must increase those numbers and all numbers in the array with index > i, then we must decrase those numbers. Let's say we are at an index i, then the cost to decrease elements before i can be given by summation of (nums[i]-nums[j]) * cost[j] for all j>=0 and j<i.Similarly to increase the elements after i, the cost is given by summation of (nums[j]-nums[i]) * cost[j] for all j>i and j<n. The total cost is cost to decrease + cost to increase. 

If we do this naively, then it will take O(n^2), but we can make use of prefix sums. We keep 2 prefix sum arrays, one is the costPrefix array and other is combinedPrefix array. costPrefix[i] stores the sum of cost till index i. combinedPrefix[i] stores the sum of (cost[i]*nums[i]). 

If you simplify the above expressions of cost to increase then it can be given by incCost = costPrefix[i-1]*p[i].first-combinedPrefix[i-1] (USE PEN AND PAPER TO VERIFY). Similarly the simplified expression for cost to decrease is decCost = (combinedPrefix[n-1]-combinedPrefix[i])-(costPrefix[n-1]-costPrefix[i])*p[i].first.

We simply have to take the minimum among all costs.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nlogn)+O(n) which is approximately O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) due tt prefix arrays and pair

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minCost(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& cost) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<pair<long,long>> p(n);

        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            p[i].first = (long long)nums[i];
            p[i].second =(long long) cost[i];
        }

        sort(p.begin(),p.end());
        vector<long long> costPrefix(n);
        vector<long long > combinedPrefix(n);

        costPrefix[0] = p[0].second;
        combinedPrefix[0] = (1LL)*(p[0].first*p[0].second);

        for(int i = 1;i<n;i++){
            costPrefix[i] = costPrefix[i-1]+p[i].second;
            combinedPrefix[i] = (1LL)*combinedPrefix[i-1]+(1LL)*(p[i].first*p[i].second);
        }

        long long ans = LONG_MAX;

        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            long long incCost = 0;
            if(i>0){
                incCost = costPrefix[i-1]*p[i].first-combinedPrefix[i-1];
            }
            long long decCost = 0;
            if(i<n){
                decCost = (combinedPrefix[n-1]-combinedPrefix[i])-(costPrefix[n-1]-costPrefix[i])*p[i].first;
            }

            long long cost = incCost+decCost;
            ans = min(ans,cost);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

