# Intuition
Think thoroughly on the paper and you will get a monotonic function like it will keep on decresing to some point than after that it will increase forever.
We have to find that lowest poinst. Therefore Binary Search will help us

# Approach
Initialise low = 0, hi = max_element(in the array nums).
Now till low <= hi , take a mid and check if the solve(mid) <= solve(mid+1) then ans = solve(mid) and hi = mid-1,  else lo = mid+1;


# Complexity
- Time complexity: ~ O(NlogN)

- Space complexity:
No extra space is used => O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long solve(int mid, vector<int> &nums, vector<int> &cost){
        long long  ans = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        for(int i = 0; i<n; i++){
            ans += (long long) abs(mid - nums[i]) * cost[i];
        }
        return ans;

    }

    long long minCost(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& cost) {
        int n = nums.size();
        long long ans = 0;
        int low = 0, hi = *max_element(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        while(low <= hi){
            int mid = low + (hi - low)/2;
            if(solve(mid, nums, cost) <= solve(mid+1, nums, cost)){
                hi = mid-1;
                ans = solve(mid, nums, cost);
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return ans;

    }
};
```

