# Intuition
The thing that came to my mind while solving this problem was to reach in the middle elemet i.e median of that rray so I calculated the median an then calculated the cost of every element to reach the median because only reahing to median will give minimum cost.

# Approach
Initialised a vector of pairs, stored elements of nums with its corresponding cost and then sorted it after that found total sum of cost and then found median. Then called a function find to calculate the cost from that median. There is a another solution too using trinary search which you can find on this submission link to optimise extra space we are using. Link - https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-cost-to-make-array-equal/submissions/976034907/

