# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

The idea is to keep moving from the smallest num value till the greatest num value keeping the track of sum of cost for values less than current num value as well as values greater than current num value. 

For ex

num = [1, 2, 6, 5]
cost = [2, 3, 10, 2]

After we sort them based on num array
num = [1, 2, 5, 6]
cost =[2, 3, 2, 10]

While traversing linearly from value i to i+1, if the current cost is currSum,  the change in cost to go from i to i+1 = currSum - rightSum + leftSum.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
There are three factors

a) currSum - stores the exact cost to convert all the num values to the iterator i

b) leftSum - stores the sum of cost for values less than the iterator i

c) rightSum -  stores the sum of cost for values greater than the iterator i.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
   public long minCost(int[] nums, int[] cost) {
        long rightSum = 0L;
        long currSum = 0L;
        int n = nums.length;
        Integer[][] arr = new Integer[n][2];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            arr[i][0]=nums[i];
            arr[i][1]=cost[i];
        }
        // Sort based on the nums array
        Arrays.sort(arr, (a,b)->a[0]-b[0]);

        // Figure out the index till where we have the value equal to first num array value
        int p = 0;
        long leftSum = 0L;
        while(p<n && arr[0][0]==arr[p][0]){
            leftSum+=arr[p][1];
            p++;
        }

        // Calculate the current cost as currSum
        for(int i=p;i<n;i++){
            rightSum+=arr[i][1];
            currSum+=(long)(Math.abs(arr[i][0]-arr[0][0])) * (long)arr[i][1];
        }
        long ans = currSum;
        // Loop linearly till the nums array greatest value
        for(int h=arr[0][0]+1;h<=arr[n-1][0];h++){
            currSum-=rightSum;
            currSum+=leftSum;

            // Remove all the indexes which have same value as h 
            while(p<n && h==arr[p][0]){
                rightSum-=arr[p][1];
                leftSum+=arr[p][1];
                p++;
            }
            ans=Math.min(ans, currSum);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

