solutions.content:
Convert this question from Weighted Median to Plain Ordinary Median by duplicating the element its cost number of times. 

For example, 1 2 3 with cost = 2,2,3, can be treated as 
1 taken 2 times = 1 1
2 taken 2 times = 2 2
3 taken 3 times = 3 3 3
 which gives, 

 1 1 2 2 3 3 3, 

 Now find the median for the new set of numbers and get your min operated element. Now, reiterate over the numbers and keep updating the number of operations by the absolute difference between the median element and the original element.

Note creating duplicate copies in reality and storing them in array will not be space-efficient. So, get catch of map for this task. Once, you get things cleared up in map, it becomes simple math and implementation.
 ___________________________________________________________________________________________________

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minCost(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& cost) 
    {
        long long int elements = 0; //total number of elements.
        map<int,long long int> mp;  // element mapped to its frequency
        for(int i=0; i<nums.size(); i++)
        {
            mp[nums[i]]+= cost[i];  //creating the map reqd.
            elements+=cost[i];      //counting total number of elements.
        }

        long long int tofind1, tofind2; //these variables will put keep track of the median element(s) position.
        if(elements%2==0)   //even
        {
            tofind1 = elements/2;       //second pos = first pos + 1
            tofind2 = tofind1+1;
        }
        else    //odd
        {
            tofind1 = (elements+1)/2;   //both the positions will be same.
            tofind2 = tofind1;
        }
        long long int median, count = 0;

        for(auto it=mp.begin();it!=mp.end();it++)
        {
            long long int ele = it->first, freq = it->second;
            if(count + freq >= tofind2) //if both the positions are within the spread of this element, then median = ele.
            {
                median = ele;
                break;
            }
            else if(count+freq == tofind1)  //if the split is across two different elements.
            {
                it++;
                median = (ele + (it->first))/2;
                break;
            }
            else    //if none matches, then continue. 
            {
                count+=freq;
            }
        }

        long long int opns = 0; // counts the total operations.

        for(auto it: mp)
        {
            long long int ele = it.first, freq = it.second;
            opns+=(abs(ele - median) * it.second);
        }

        return opns;
    }
};
```

