solutions.content:
Just like the peak in the array, this is the similiar question with some few changes.
The main idea of the algo is that there is a dip in the array we when draw all the cost to make numbers from 1 to maxElement in the array, you will observe a dip, that dip is our ans. And using Binary Search we can try those numbers and we'll also calculate the cost to make the next element that will help us in defining the direction for BS.


```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minCost(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& cost) {
        long long ans = LONG_LONG_MAX;
        int n = cost.size();

        int low = 0, high = *max_element(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        while (low <= high) {
            long long mid = low + (high - low) / 2LL;

            long long curr_cost = 0, other_cost = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                curr_cost += abs(mid - nums[i]) * cost[i]; // this is the currCost
                other_cost += abs(mid + 1 - nums[i]) * cost[i]; // and this is the cost which will help us to move whether left or right
            }

            ans = min(ans, curr_cost);

            if (curr_cost <= other_cost) {
                high = mid - 1;
            }
            else {
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

